Limit search Enter what to search for: Total document storage, complete document, current structure.
Search with operators
Use operators to achieve the required search results. If you enter two terms without an operator, all hits are shown which contain both terms (corresponds to AND). This is the default search setting. Note: When using + or – there no space between the operator and term. AND = + Hits which contain all terms. E.g.: Data AND Block; Data +Block OR Hits which have at least one of the entered terms. E.g.: Data OR Block; Data Block
NOT = - Hits which do not contain the negated term . E.g.: Data NOT Block; Data -Block EXACT = “ “ Hits which contain exactly the entered term. E.g.: “smart card“
Integrated Terminology If you receive unexpected search results for the term entered, it is due to a searched term being deprecated. The PUD Manager automatically searched for the new term and delivers search results which correspond to the new terminology.
